cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on deep learning for neuroimaging classification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel model architecture, which involves reinforcement learning, making it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning for automated biomarker discovery, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of recurrent neural networks and attention mechanisms also suggests relevance to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for automated diagnosis, which involves natural language processing and medical terminology, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category as well.
